26/01/2006
ROME, Italy -- Enhancing bilateral ties is the focus of Greek President Karolos Papoulias' five-day visit to Italy. He and Prime Minister Silvio Berlusconi discussed ways to boost bilateral co-operation in the economic, trade and cultural sectors on Wednesday (25 January). Papoulias is also to meet with Pope Benedict XVI. (ANA, MPA, Kathimerini - 25/01/06)
